Subject: Re: [T2] External Oil Cooler Kits Whose to Use?

At 09:39 AM 6/25/2003, Theodore Reshetiloff wrote:
>I am going to add an external cooler to my 78' type IV motor and am looking
>for some help deciding what route to go.

I recommend you not add an external cooler.  :-)

>I think I will mount the cooler under the cargo floor area of the
>bus horizintally.

How are you planning on protecting it from road hazards?

> Do you guys think the air flow there will be good or
>should I try to locate the cooler somewhere where I can get better airflow
>through the cooler, if so where?

There really isn't a good place that gets "natural" airflow.  An electric fan can solve this problem, allowing you to put the cooler almost anywhere.  It also makes it somewhat easier to maintain oil temperature (you can utilize a thermostat to switch the fan on and off).

> Oil temps on the bus have approaced 250
>when pushing it hard on a warm day, sump mounted VDO sender and gauge.

That's not very hot... if you have good oil pressure and synthetic oil.

-David
